    "The ground motion not only affected the Nepalese terrain right after the earthquake through co-seismic landslides, but its disturbance increased landslide susceptibility in the following years, a phenomenon commonly referred to as earthquake legacy (Jones et al., 2021; Tanyaş et al., 2021a).",
    "The legacy of the Gorkha earthquake has been recently demonstrated by mapping a multi-temporal inventory, which has been publicly shared by Kincey et al. (2021)."
